{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775823379142,"sessionID":"ses_288b0ff60ffeuyGWwUCsvQJrX9","part":{"id":"prt_d774f1def001gZhvZ2bITMWZUe","messageID":"msg_d774f0cca001hfBw7AHlsAFt2m","sessionID":"ses_288b0ff60ffeuyGWwUCsvQJrX9","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_c76cdae70042472d8486dd25","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore workloadmanager module","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project's pkg/workloadmanager module thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The directory structure under pkg/workloadmanager\n2. All Go files and their purposes\n3. Existing GC or cleanup mechanisms\n4. Sandbox-related code and how sandboxes are managed\n5. Any existing timer/cron/scheduled task patterns\n6. Configuration structures related to workloadmanager\n7. How sandboxes are created, tracked, and deleted\n\nSearch in the workspace root /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z and any agentcube reference code that might exist.\n\nAlso search for any existing spec files, architecture documents, or design docs related to AR-008 or Sandbox GC.\n\nReturn:\n- Full directory listing of pkg/workloadmanager\n- Key code snippets showing sandbox lifecycle management\n- Any existing GC/cleanup patterns\n- Configuration structs\n- Relevant interfaces and types","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288b0cd95ffeBV7Glus0Fkr65g (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the entire `pkg/workloadmanager` module. Here is the complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Full Directory Structure of `pkg/workloadmanager`\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── handler/                    (7 files)\n│   ├── constants.go            - GVRs, labels, annotations, default constants\n│   ├── models.go               - Request/Response structs, SandboxInfo, SandboxStatus\n│   ├── sandbox_create.go       - Sandbox creation handler (AgentRuntime + CodeInterpreter)\n│   ├── sandbox_delete.go       - Sandbox deletion handler (by session ID or by name)\n│   ├── sandbox_delete_test.go  - Deletion handler tests + mockStore\n│   ├── sandbox_lifecycle.go    - LifecycleManager: TTL-based GC, status, list, extend TTL\n│   └── sandbox_lifecycle_test.go - LifecycleManager tests (696 lines)\n├── middleware/                 (0 files - empty directory)\n├── reconciler/                 (8 files)\n│   ├── agentruntime.go         - Reconcile AgentRuntime CRD lifecycle\n│   ├── codeinterpreter.go      - Reconcile CodeInterpreter CRD lifecycle\n│   ├── event_handlers.go       - Informer event handlers (Add/Update/Delete for AR, CI, Pod)\n│   ├── metrics.go              - PrometheusMetricsRecorder implementation\n│   ├── pod.go                  - Reconcile Pod events (update PodIP)\n│   ├── reconciler.go           - SandboxReconciler main struct, Run(), event registration\n│   ├── sync.go                 - syncHandler, processNextWorkItem, runWorker\n│   └── types.go                - Store interface, MetricsRecorder interface, ReconcilerDeps, constants\n└── response/                   (2 files)\n    ├── response.go             - JSON/Created/Error/ErrorWithID helpers\n    └── response_test.go        - Response helper tests\n```\n\n**Total: 17 Go files** (15 source + 2 test-only in response; handler has additional test files)\n\n---\n\n## 2. All Go Files and Their Purposes\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `handler/constants.go` | Defines GVRs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Sandbox, SandboxClaim), label keys, annotation keys, and default TTL/idle timeout constants |\n| `handler/models.go` | Core data types: `CreateSandboxRequest`, `CreateSandboxResponse`, `SandboxInfo`, `SandboxStatus`, `EntryPoint` |\n| `handler/sandbox_create.go` | HTTP handlers for creating AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter sandboxes; builds CR objects, watches for readiness, resolves PodIP |\n| `handler/sandbox_delete.go` | HTTP handlers for deleting sandboxes by session ID or by name/namespace/kind |\n| `handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go` | **LifecycleManager** -- the existing GC mechanism: ticker-based expired sandbox cleanup, status API, list API, TTL extension API |\n| `handler/sandbox_lifecycle_test.go` | Comprehensive tests for LifecycleManager (expiration, TTL extension, list filtering, cleanup) |\n| `handler/sandbox_delete_test.go` | Tests for delete handler + `mockStore` implementation |\n| `reconciler/types.go` | `Store` interface (reconciler view), `MetricsRecorder` interface, `ReconcilerDeps`, status constants |\n| `reconciler/reconciler.go` | `SandboxReconciler` struct, `NewSandboxReconciler()`, `Run()` with informer factory, workqueue setup |\n| `reconciler/sync.go` | `syncHandler()` dispatches to AR/CI/Pod reconcilers; `processNextWorkItem()` with retry logic (max 15 retries) |\n| `reconciler/agentruntime.go` | `reconcileAgentRuntime()` -- stores/updates/deletes sandboxes based on AgentRuntime CR state |\n| `reconciler/codeinterpreter.go` | `reconcileCodeInterpreter()` -- stores/updates/deletes sandboxes based on CodeInterpreter CR state; handles warm pool |\n| `reconciler/pod.go` | `reconcilePod()` -- updates sandbox PodIP when Pod becomes running |\n| `reconciler/event_handlers.go` | Informer event handlers: enqueue keys on Add/Update/Delete for AR, CI, and Pod resources |\n| `reconciler/metrics.go` | `PrometheusMetricsRecorder` -- exposes reconcile_total, reconcile_duration, reconcile_errors, workqueue_depth, workqueue_adds |\n| `response/response.go` | HTTP response helpers: `JSON()`, `Created()`, `Error()`, `ErrorWithID()` |\n| `response/response_test.go` | Tests for response helpers |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing GC / Cleanup Mechanisms\n\n### 3.1 LifecycleManager GC (in `handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go`)\n\nThis is the **primary existing GC mechanism**. It uses a `time.Ticker` to periodically clean up expired sandboxes:\n\n```go\n// Lines 79-93: The cleanup loop\nfunc (m *LifecycleManager) runCleanupLoop(ctx context.Context) {\n    ticker := time.NewTicker(m.checkInterval)  // default: 5 minutes\n    defer ticker.Stop()\n\n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            return\n        case <-m.stopCh:\n            return\n        case <-ticker.C:\n            m.cleanupExpiredSandboxes(ctx)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n```go\n// Lines 95-115: Expired sandbox cleanup\nfunc (m *LifecycleManager) cleanupExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context) {\n    sandboxes, err := m.store.ListSandboxes(ctx)\n    if err != nil {\n        log.Printf(\"failed to list sandboxes for cleanup: %v\", err)\n        return\n    }\n\n    now := time.Now()\n    var expired []*SandboxInfo\n    for _, sb := range sandboxes {\n        if m.isExpired(sb, now) {\n            expired = append(expired, sb)\n        }\n    }\n\n    for _, sb := range expired {\n        if err := m.deleteSandbox(ctx, sb); err != nil {\n            log.Printf(\"failed to delete expired sandbox %s/%s: %v\", sb.Namespace, sb.SandboxName, err)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n```go\n// Lines 117-127: Expiration check logic\nfunc (m *LifecycleManager) isExpired(info *SandboxInfo, now time.Time) bool {\n    if !info.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n        return !now.Before(info.ExpiresAt)\n    }\n    if !info.CreatedAt.IsZero() {\n        return !now.Before(info.CreatedAt.Add(m.defaultTTL))  // default: 8 hours\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n```go\n// Lines 129-153: Delete sandbox (CR + Store entry)\nfunc (m *LifecycleManager) deleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *SandboxInfo) error {\n    gvr, err := m.resolveGVR(info.Kind)\n    // ...\n    err = m.dynamicClient.Resource(gvr).Namespace(info.Namespace).Delete(deleteCtx, info.SandboxName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n    // ...\n    if err := m.store.DeleteSandbox(ctx, info.SessionID); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to delete sandbox from store: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Reconciler-Driven Cleanup (event-driven, not timer-based)\n\nThe `SandboxReconciler` in `reconciler/` performs cleanup when CRDs are deleted or terminated:\n\n**From `reconciler/agentruntime.go` (lines 59-67):**\n```go\nif ar.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n    log.Printf(\"[reconciler] AgentRuntime %s/%s is being deleted, cleaning up session %s\", namespace, name, sessionID)\n    if err := r.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID); err != nil {\n        // ...\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n**From `reconciler/agentruntime.go` (lines 108-116):**\n```go\nif status == StatusTerminated {\n    log.Printf(\"[reconciler] AgentRuntime %s/%s terminated, cleaning up session %s\", namespace, name, sessionID)\n    if err := r.store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID); err != nil {\n        // ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Same pattern in `reconciler/codeinterpreter.go` (lines 40-48 and 89-97).**\n\n### 3.3 Idle Cleanup (agentd component, separate from workloadmanager)\n\nDocumented in `idle-cleanup/design.md` -- a separate controller-runtime reconciler in `pkg/agentd` that:\n- Reads `last-activity-time` annotation on Sandbox CRs\n- Uses `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n- Deletes Sandbox when `time.Now().After(lastActivity + SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n- Requeues with `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)` for precision\n\n### 3.4 Documented but NOT Yet Implemented: Garbage Collector\n\nThe `sandbox-orchestration/design.md` documents a planned `garbageCollector` struct:\n```go\nconst gcOnceTimeout = 2 * time.Minute\n\ntype garbageCollector struct {\n    k8sClient   *K8sClient\n    interval    time.Duration   // 15 seconds\n    storeClient store.Store\n}\n```\n- Would call `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout), 16)` and `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, time.Now(), 16)`\n- **This code does NOT exist in the current codebase** -- only documented in design files.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Sandbox-Related Code and Management\n\n### 4.1 Sandbox Creation Flow (`handler/sandbox_create.go`)\n\n1. **Request validation** -- `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` checks kind, namespace, name\n2. **Template lookup** -- Fetches AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter template from informer cache\n3. **Session/Sandbox name generation** -- UUID for session ID, `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}` for sandbox name\n4. **CR construction** -- Builds `unstructured.Unstructured` Sandbox CR with labels, annotations, spec\n5. **Store pre-registration** -- `store.StoreSandbox()` with status \"pending\"\n6. **Watch for readiness** -- `reconciler.WatchSandboxOnce()` returns a channel\n7. **CR creation** -- `dynClient.Resource(gvr).Namespace(ns).Create()`\n8. **Wait for running** -- 2-minute timeout, rollback on failure\n9. **PodIP resolution** -- Multiple strategies: direct get, annotation lookup, label selector\n10. **Store update** -- `store.UpdateSandbox()` with status \"running\", PodIP, entry points\n\n### 4.2 Sandbox Tracking\n\nSandboxes are tracked via the `Store` interface with two slightly different signatures:\n\n**Reconciler Store (`reconciler/types.go`, lines 42-48):**\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *handler.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *handler.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*handler.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*handler.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Handler Store (`handler/sandbox_create.go`, lines 30-36):**\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n    DeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\nNote: The two `Store` interfaces have **slightly different signatures** -- the reconciler version takes `sessionID` as a separate parameter for `StoreSandbox`, while the handler version embeds it in `SandboxInfo`. The reconciler version returns `map[string]*SandboxInfo` from `ListSandboxes`, while the handler returns `[]*SandboxInfo`.\n\n### 4.3 Sandbox Deletion Flow (`handler/sandbox_delete.go`)\n\n1. Lookup sandbox by session ID in Store\n2. Resolve GVR based on Kind (Sandbox or SandboxClaim)\n3. Delete CR from K8s cluster via dynamic client (30s timeout)\n4. Delete entry from Store\n5. Handles idempotent deletion (if CR already gone, still cleans Store)\n\n### 4.4 SandboxInfo Model (`handler/models.go`, lines 40-52)\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    SessionID    string       `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxName  string       `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    SandboxID    string       `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    WorkloadName string       `json:\"workloadName\"`\n    Namespace    string       `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Kind         string       `json:\"kind\"`\n    PodIP        string       `json:\"podIp,omitempty\"`\n    EntryPoints  []EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt    time.Time    `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt    time.Time    `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status       string       `json:\"status\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Timer/Cron/Scheduled Task Patterns\n\n### 5.1 LifecycleManager Ticker (the ONLY timer pattern in the codebase)\n\n**File:** `handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go`, line 80\n\n```go\nticker := time.NewTicker(m.checkInterval)  // default: 5 minutes\n```\n\nThis is the **only** `time.NewTicker` usage in the entire `pkg/workloadmanager` module.\n\n### 5.2 Reconciler Workqueue Rate Limiter (not a timer, but time-based retry)\n\n**File:** `reconciler/reconciler.go`, lines 50-53\n\n```go\nwq := workqueue.NewNamedRateLimitingQueue(\n    workqueue.NewItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter(5*time.Second, 5*time.Minute),\n    \"sandbox-reconciler\",\n)\n```\n\n### 5.3 Timeouts (context-based, not scheduled)\n\n| Location | Timeout | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|---------|\n| `reconciler/reconciler.go:159` | 30s | Cache sync timeout |\n| `reconciler/reconciler.go:192` | 30s | Shutdown timeout |\n| `handler/sandbox_create.go:183` | 2min | Sandbox creation wait |\n| `handler/sandbox_create.go:370` | 30s | Rollback CR deletion |\n| `handler/sandbox_delete.go:124` | 30s | Sandbox deletion |\n| `handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go:135` | 30s | Expired sandbox deletion |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Configuration Structures\n\n### 6.1 LifecycleManagerDeps (`handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go`, lines 20-25)\n\n```go\ntype LifecycleManagerDeps struct {\n    DynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n    Store         Store\n    CheckInterval time.Duration  // default: 5 minutes\n    DefaultTTL    time.Duration  // default: 8 hours\n}\n```\n\n### 6.2 SandboxCreateHandlerDeps (`handler/sandbox_create.go`, lines 46-56)\n\n```go\ntype SandboxCreateHandlerDeps struct {\n    DynamicClient     dynamic.Interface\n    Clientset         clientset.Interface\n    KubeClientset     kubernetes.Interface\n    InformerFactory   externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n    Store             Store\n    Reconciler        SandboxReconcilerWatcher\n    TokenCache        TokenCache\n    UserClientFactory UserClientFactory\n    EnableAuth        bool\n}\n```\n\n### 6.3 SandboxDeleteHandlerDeps (`handler/sandbox_delete.go`, lines 20-27)\n\n```go\ntype SandboxDeleteHandlerDeps struct {\n    DynamicClient   dynamic.Interface\n    Clientset       clientset.Interface\n    InformerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n    Store           Store\n    EnableAuth      bool\n    TokenCache      TokenCache\n}\n```\n\n### 6.4 ReconcilerDeps (`reconciler/types.go`, lines 58-67)\n\n```go\ntype ReconcilerDeps struct {\n    Clientset       clientset.Interface\n    InformerFactory externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n    ARLister        listers.AgentRuntimeLister\n    CILister        listers.CodeInterpreterLister\n    PodInformer     coreinformers.PodInformer\n    Store           Store\n    Workers         int\n    MetricsRecorder MetricsRecorder\n}\n```\n\n### 6.5 Constants (`handler/constants.go`)\n\n```go\nconst (\n    DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8     // hours\n    DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15    // minutes\n)\n\nconst (\n    LabelManagedBy      = \"app.kubernetes.io/managed-by\"\n    LabelManagedByValue = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"\n    LabelSessionID      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n    LabelWorkloadName   = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n    LabelSandboxName    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n)\n\nconst (\n    AnnotationIdleTimeout    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n    AnnotationSandboxPodName = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n)\n```\n\n### 6.6 Reconciler Constants (`reconciler/types.go`)\n\n```go\nconst (\n    maxRetries       = 15\n    defaultWorkers   = 2\n    cacheSyncTimeout = 30 * time.Second\n    shutdownTimeout  = 30 * time.Second\n)\n\nconst (\n    StatusPending    = \"pending\"\n    StatusRunning    = \"running\"\n    StatusTerminated = \"terminated\"\n)\n```\n\n### 6.7 Documented Config (from sandbox-orchestration/design.md, NOT in current code)\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port             string\n    RuntimeClassName string\n    EnableTLS        bool\n    TLSCert          string\n    TLSKey           string\n    EnableAuth       bool\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Sandbox Lifecycle: Create, Track, Delete\n\n### Creation Flow\n\n```\nPOST /v1/agent-runtime  OR  POST /v1/code-interpreter\n    |\n    v\nSandboxCreateHandler.CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox() / CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox()\n    |\n    +-- Validate request\n    +-- Lookup template from informer cache\n    +-- Generate sessionID (UUID) and sandboxName ({workload}-{random8})\n    +-- Build Sandbox CR (unstructured) with labels + annotations\n    +-- StoreSandbox() -> status \"pending\"\n    +-- WatchSandboxOnce() -> get watcher channel\n    +-- Create CR via dynamic client\n    +-- Wait for \"running\" status (2min timeout)\n    +-- Resolve PodIP\n    +-- UpdateSandbox() -> status \"running\", PodIP, EntryPoints\n    +-- Return CreateSandboxResponse\n```\n\n### Tracking Flow\n\n```\nInformer Events (Add/Update/Delete)\n    |\n    v\nevent_handlers.go -> enqueue key to workqueue\n    |\n    v\nsync.go -> syncHandler() -> determine resource type (AR/CI/Pod)\n    |\n    +-- AgentRuntime: reconcileAgentRuntime()\n    |       +-- If DeletionTimestamp != nil -> DeleteSandboxBySessionID()\n    |       +-- If new -> StoreSandbox()\n    |       +-- If status changed -> UpdateSandbox()\n    |       +-- If terminated -> DeleteSandboxBySessionID()\n    |\n    +-- CodeInterpreter: reconcileCodeInterpreter()\n    |       (same pattern as AgentRuntime)\n    |\n    +-- Pod: reconcilePod()\n            +-- Update PodIP in Store\n```\n\n### Deletion Flow (Three Paths)\n\n**Path 1: Explicit API Delete**\n```\nDELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n    -> SandboxDeleteHandler.DeleteSandbox()\n    -> Delete CR from K8s\n    -> DeleteSandbox() from Store\n```\n\n**Path 2: Reconciler-Driven (CR deletion or termination)**\n```\nAgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter DeletionTimestamp set OR status=Terminated\n    -> reconciler detects change\n    -> DeleteSandboxBySessionID() from Store\n```\n\n**Path 3: GC Timer (LifecycleManager)**\n```\nEvery 5 minutes (checkInterval):\n    -> ListSandboxes() from Store\n    -> For each: isExpired() check (ExpiresAt or CreatedAt+TTL)\n    -> deleteSandbox() -> Delete CR + Delete from Store\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. AR-008: Sandbox GC Design Document\n\n**Location:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-008/`\n\n**Files:**\n- `proposal.md` -- Detailed proposal (145 lines)\n- `design.md` -- Skeleton design template (33 lines, mostly empty section headers)\n- `tasks.md` -- Task list placeholder (14 lines, \"to be detailed\")\n\n**Key Points from AR-008 Proposal:**\n\nThe proposal identifies **5 gaps** in the current GC mechanism:\n\n1. **No idle timeout cleanup** -- `AnnotationIdleTimeout` is set on sandboxes (default 15 min) but GC does not read it or track `LastActivityAt`\n2. **No orphan CR cleanup** -- If Store entry is deleted but K8s CR remains, GC cannot find it\n3. **No ghost entry cleanup** -- If K8s CR is deleted externally but Store entry remains\n4. **No GC metrics** -- No observability into GC health\n5. **Unstructured logging** -- Uses `log.Printf` instead of structured logging\n\n**Proposed additions:**\n- `SandboxInfo.LastActivityAt` field\n- Idle timeout check in GC loop\n- `cleanupOrphanCRs()` method (list CRs with session-id label, diff against Store)\n- Ghost entry cleanup (Store entries with no matching K8s CR)\n- `GCMetrics` struct with `IncCleanupTotal(reason)`, `ObserveCleanupDuration()`, `IncCleanupErrors(reason)`\n- Switch to `slog` for structured logging\n- `MaxOrphanScanLimit` = 100 per GC cycle\n\n**Selected approach:** Enhance existing `LifecycleManager` GC loop (single ticker, sequential sub-tasks).\n\n**Status:** Not yet implemented (proposal reviewed, tasks not yet broken down).\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288b0cd95ffeBV7Glus0Fkr65g","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore workloadmanager module","time":{"start":1775823172199,"end":1775823379130}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775823379197,"sessionID":"ses_288b0ff60ffeuyGWwUCsvQJrX9","part":{"id":"prt_d77525ac5001b5MNzbdagPv3Y4","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d774f0cca001hfBw7AHlsAFt2m","sessionID":"ses_288b0ff60ffeuyGWwUCsvQJrX9","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19641,"input":19234,"output":273,"reasoning":134,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.005980541}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775823380502,"sessionID":"ses_288b0ff60ffeuyGWwUCsvQJrX9","part":{"id":"prt_d77526013001a07pTX8V8wkr6a","messageID":"msg_d77525b13001dxfa8pb3sHJ8c8","sessionID":"ses_288b0ff60ffeuyGWwUCsvQJrX9","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775823445259,"sessionID":"ses_288b0ff60ffeuyGWwUCsvQJrX9","part":{"id":"prt_d77526d8d001cpeH7u3HEewBMO","messageID":"msg_d77525b13001dxfa8pb3sHJ8c8","sessionID":"ses_288b0ff60ffeuyGWwUCsvQJrX9","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_8b0b9c501f5b4125b795ac3d","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n\n## Context\n\nThe existing `LifecycleManager` in `handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go` runs a ticker-based GC loop that cleans up sandboxes expired by `ExpiresAt` or `CreatedAt + defaultTTL`. This spec adds four missing GC capabilities identified in the AR-008 proposal:\n\n1. **Idle timeout cleanup** — sandboxes inactive beyond their idle timeout annotation\n2. **Orphan CR cleanup** — K8s CRs whose Store entry is gone\n3. **Ghost entry cleanup** — Store entries whose K8s CR is gone\n4. **GC metrics** — observability into GC health\n\nStructured logging (`slog`) replaces `log.Printf` throughout the GC code path.\n\nThe selected approach enhances the existing `LifecycleManager` GC loop with sequential sub-tasks per tick.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement 1: Idle Timeout Cleanup\n\nThe GC loop shall detect and delete sandboxes that have exceeded their idle timeout, where idle timeout is specified per-sandbox via the `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` annotation (default 15 minutes).\n\n### GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n**Scenario 1.1: Sandbox exceeds idle timeout**\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in the Store with `Status = \"running\"` and `LastActivityAt` set to a time older than its idle timeout\n- **WHEN** the GC cleanup cycle runs\n- **THEN** the sandbox CR is deleted from the Kubernetes cluster\n- **AND** the sandbox entry is removed from the Store\n- **AND** the GC metrics counter `cleanup_total{reason=\"idle\"}` is incremented\n\n**Scenario 1.2: Sandbox within idle timeout is preserved**\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in the Store with `Status = \"running\"` and `LastActivityAt` set to a time within its idle timeout window\n- **WHEN** the GC cleanup cycle runs\n- **THEN** the sandbox is NOT deleted\n- **AND** the sandbox remains in the Store with its existing status\n\n**Scenario 1.3: Sandbox with no LastActivityAt falls back to TTL**\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in the Store with `Status = \"running\"` and `LastActivityAt` is zero/unset\n- **WHEN** the GC cleanup cycle runs\n- **THEN** the sandbox expiration is evaluated using `CreatedAt + defaultTTL` (existing TTL logic)\n- **AND** the idle timeout check is skipped for this sandbox\n\n**Scenario 1.4: Per-sandbox idle timeout from annotation**\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox has the annotation `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` set to `\"30m\"`\n- **WHEN** the GC evaluates idle timeout for this sandbox\n- **THEN** the GC uses 30 minutes as the idle timeout threshold instead of the global default (15 minutes)\n\n**Scenario 1.5: Sandbox in \"pending\" status is not idle-cleaned**\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox exists in the Store with `Status = \"pending\"` and `LastActivityAt` is older than idle timeout\n- **WHEN** the GC cleanup cycle runs\n- **THEN** the sandbox is NOT deleted for idle timeout (pending sandboxes are still initializing)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement 2: Orphan CR Cleanup\n\nThe GC loop shall detect and delete Kubernetes CRs (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter) that have a `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id` label but no corresponding entry in the Store.\n\n### GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n**Scenario 2.1: Orphan CR is detected and deleted**\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists in the cluster with label `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id=abc-123`\n- **AND** no sandbox entry with `SessionID = \"abc-123\"` exists in the Store\n- **WHEN** the GC orphan scan sub-task runs\n- **THEN** the orphan CR is deleted from the Kubernetes cluster\n- **AND** the GC metrics counter `cleanup_total{reason=\"orphan_cr\"}` is incremented\n\n**Scenario 2.2: CR with matching Store entry is preserved**\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR exists with label `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id=def-456`\n- **AND** a sandbox entry with `SessionID = \"def-456\"` exists in the Store\n- **WHEN** the GC orphan scan sub-task runs\n- **THEN** the CR is NOT deleted\n\n**Scenario 2.3: Orphan scan respects pagination limit**\n- **GIVEN** there are 150 CRs with the `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id` label across all namespaces\n- **AND** `MaxOrphanScanLimit` is set to 100\n- **WHEN** the GC orphan scan sub-task runs\n- **THEN** only the first 100 CRs are scanned in this cycle\n- **AND** remaining CRs will be scanned in subsequent cycles\n\n**Scenario 2.4: Orphan scan handles both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs**\n- **GIVEN** an orphan AgentRuntime CR and an orphan CodeInterpreter CR both exist without Store entries\n- **WHEN** the GC orphan scan sub-task runs\n- **THEN** both orphan CRs are deleted\n\n---\n\n## Requirement 3: Ghost Entry Cleanup\n\nThe GC loop shall detect and remove Store entries for sandboxes whose corresponding Kubernetes CR no longer exists.\n\n### GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n**Scenario 3.1: Ghost Store entry is cleaned up**\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox entry exists in the Store with `SessionID = \"ghi-789\"` and `Kind = \"AgentRuntime\"`\n- **AND** no AgentRuntime CR with name matching `SandboxName` exists in the specified namespace\n- **WHEN** the GC ghost entry scan sub-task runs\n- **THEN** the ghost entry is removed from the Store\n- **AND** the GC metrics counter `cleanup_total{reason=\"ghost_entry\"}` is incremented\n\n**Scenario 3.2: Valid sandbox with existing CR is preserved**\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox entry exists in the Store\n- **AND** the corresponding Kubernetes CR (by name, namespace, and kind) exists in the cluster\n- **WHEN** the GC ghost entry scan sub-task runs\n- **THEN** the Store entry is NOT deleted\n\n**Scenario 3.3: Ghost scan handles both kinds**\n- **GIVEN** a ghost Store entry for an AgentRuntime sandbox and a ghost entry for a CodeInterpreter sandbox both exist\n- **WHEN** the GC ghost entry scan sub-task runs\n- **THEN** both ghost entries are removed from the Store\n\n---\n\n## Requirement 4: GC Metrics\n\nThe GC subsystem shall expose Prometheus metrics for cleanup operations, duration, and errors.\n\n### GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n**Scenario 4.1: Cleanup total counter by reason**\n- **GIVEN** a `GCMetrics` recorder is wired into the `LifecycleManager`\n- **WHEN** a sandbox is deleted for idle timeout\n- **THEN** the counter `agentcube_gc_cleanup_total{reason=\"idle\"}` is incremented by 1\n\n- **WHEN** a sandbox is deleted for TTL expiration\n- **THEN** the counter `agentcube_gc_cleanup_total{reason=\"ttl_expired\"}` is incremented by 1\n\n- **WHEN** an orphan CR is deleted\n- **THEN** the counter `agentcube_gc_cleanup_total{reason=\"orphan_cr\"}` is incremented by 1\n\n- **WHEN** a ghost entry is removed\n- **THEN** the counter `agentcube_gc_cleanup_total{reason=\"ghost_entry\"}` is incremented by 1\n\n**Scenario 4.2: Cleanup duration histogram**\n- **GIVEN** a GC cleanup cycle completes (all sub-tasks)\n- **WHEN** the cycle finishes\n- **THEN** the histogram `agentcube_gc_cleanup_duration_seconds` records the total cycle duration\n\n**Scenario 4.3: Cleanup error counter**\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox deletion fails during the GC cycle (e.g., K8s API error)\n- **WHEN** the error is caught and logged\n- **THEN** the counter `agentcube_gc_cleanup_errors_total{reason=\"<failure_reason>\"}` is incremented by 1\n\n**Scenario 4.4: MetricsRecorder interface**\n- **GIVEN** the `MetricsRecorder` interface in `reconciler/types.go`\n- **WHEN** a new `GCMetrics` type is defined\n- **THEN** it implements `IncCleanupTotal(reason string)`, `ObserveCleanupDuration(seconds float64)`, and `IncCleanupErrors(reason string)`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement 5: Structured Logging\n\nAll GC-related log output shall use Go's `slog` package with structured key-value fields instead of `log.Printf`.\n\n### GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n**Scenario 5.1: GC cycle start log**\n- **WHEN** a GC cleanup cycle begins\n- **THEN** a structured log entry is emitted with level `INFO` containing fields: `event=\"gc_cycle_start\"`, `check_interval`, `default_ttl`\n\n**Scenario 5.2: Sandbox deletion log**\n- **WHEN** a sandbox is deleted by the GC (for any reason)\n- **THEN** a structured log entry is emitted with level `INFO` containing fields: `event=\"sandbox_deleted\"`, `session_id`, `sandbox_name`, `namespace`, `kind`, `reason`\n\n**Scenario 5.3: GC error log**\n- **WHEN** a GC sub-task encounters an error (e.g., failed to list sandboxes, failed to delete CR)\n- **THEN** a structured log entry is emitted with level `ERROR` containing fields: `event=\"gc_error\"`, `sub_task`, `error`, and relevant context fields\n\n**Scenario 5.4: GC cycle completion log**\n- **WHEN** a GC cleanup cycle completes\n- **THEN** a structured log entry is emitted with level `INFO` containing fields: `event=\"gc_cycle_complete\"`, `duration_ms`, `ttl_cleaned`, `idle_cleaned`, `orphan_cleaned`, `ghost_cleaned`, `errors`\n\n---\n\n## Data Model Changes\n\n### SandboxInfo (handler/models.go)\n\nAdd field:\n\n```go\nLastActivityAt time.Time `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n```\n\n- Zero value means \"not tracked for idle timeout\" — fallback to TTL-based expiration.\n- Set during sandbox creation to `CreatedAt`.\n- Updated by the reconciler when activity is detected (out of scope for this spec; field is added for future use).\n\n### LifecycleManagerDeps (handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go)\n\nAdd fields:\n\n```go\nDefaultIdleTimeout time.Duration  // default: 15 minutes\nMaxOrphanScanLimit int            // default: 100\nMetricsRecorder    GCMetrics      // optional; nil disables metrics\n```\n\n### GCMetrics (new type in handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go or reconciler/metrics.go)\n\n```go\ntype GCMetrics interface {\n    IncCleanupTotal(reason string)\n    ObserveCleanupDuration(seconds float64)\n    IncCleanupErrors(reason string)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Behavior Specification\n\n### GC Cycle Execution Order\n\nEach tick of the GC loop executes sub-tasks sequentially in this order:\n\n1. **TTL expiration cleanup** (existing behavior, enhanced with metrics + structured logging)\n2. **Idle timeout cleanup** (new)\n3. **Orphan CR scan** (new)\n4. **Ghost entry scan** (new)\n5. **Log cycle summary and record metrics** (new)\n\nThe cycle continues on the next tick regardless of errors in individual sub-tasks (errors are logged and counted, not fatal).\n\n### Idle Timeout Resolution\n\nFor each running sandbox:\n1. If `LastActivityAt` is zero → skip idle check (TTL handles it)\n2. Read `AnnotationIdleTimeout` from the sandbox's CR annotations (via dynamic client or cached informer)\n3. If annotation is absent or unparseable → use `DefaultIdleTimeout` (15 minutes)\n4. If `time.Now().After(LastActivityAt + idleTimeout)` → mark for deletion\n\n### Orphan CR Detection\n\n1. List all AgentRuntime CRs cluster-wide (or in managed namespaces) with label `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`, limited to `MaxOrphanScanLimit`\n2. List all CodeInterpreter CRs similarly\n3. For each CR, check if its session-id exists in the Store\n4. If not found → delete the CR\n\n### Ghost Entry Detection\n\n1. List all sandbox entries from the Store\n2. For each entry, check if the corresponding CR exists (by name, namespace, kind) via dynamic client\n3. If CR not found → remove the Store entry\n\n---\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Updating `LastActivityAt` on sandbox activity (reconciler-side change; this spec only adds the field and the GC read path)\n- Changing the GC tick interval (remains configurable via `CheckInterval`, default 5 minutes)\n- Warm pool sandbox GC (warm pool sandboxes are managed separately in the CodeInterpreter reconciler)\n- Changing the Store interface signature (new methods may be added but existing signatures are preserved)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775823445251,"end":1775823445256}}}}
